The paper discusses a modulation technique for wireless optical systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions visible light communications (VLC), which is a subfield of optical communications (cs.OH). The use of interleaving to combat inter-symbol interference (ISI) suggests a possible connection to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL), while the discussion of power efficiency and nonlinearity may relate to multimedia (cs.MM).
